pr_title: Setting up the project and its dependencies
pr_body:
Fixes: #1

> I had already pushed the initial code for project setup with Vite along with adding -
> - Vuetify
> - Vue-router
> - Pinia.

 
 In this PR, 

1.  I have added EsLint + Prettier to the project 
 Also added the scripts
-  `npm run lint` for showing all the EsLint errors
-  `npm run format` for formatting the entire project using the rules set in the `.prettierrc` file
    and formatted the code previously pushed using EsLint and Prettier rules.

2.  Added Vue-i18n to the project, made a local folder to set up localization & to contain data for several languages
 
 @tachyons @abstrekt @ayan-biswas0412 
 can you please review it.

pr_body:
Fixes : #3 

In this PR,

1.  Imported the simulator code from the CircuitVerse repository.

2.  I used my GSoC task's dummy Vue Component from simulator HTML. 
So Navbar is already broken down into smaller components 
(Options API needs to be updated to Composition API and some other changes to be done).

3.  Imported simulator stylesheets into styles folder. 
     Styles will be refactored later to its specefic components.

4.  jQuery UI not working so I commented those elements. 
So accordion, dialogBox, draggable, and resizable not working.
Will replace these using Vuetify.

5.  Added pre-commit-hook `Husky` and `Commitlint` to check on the commits.

6.  Redirected `/` route to `/simulator`

7.  Added dependencies necessary for the simulator to be working.
(added Bootstrap temporarily)

The simulator's core functionalities are working properly.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/61665451/174111015-443cc62e-e8b7-454e-a23a-e5a74dba2d34.mp4



**To-do :** Fix EsLint errors in simulator javascript files.

pr_body:
Fixes: #6 
- Created PanelHeader Vue file - common for all panels which take in the title as a prop and display it.

- Converted the jQuery UI accordion -> [Vuetify expansion panel (variant: accordion)](https://next.vuetifyjs.com/en/components/expansion-panels/)

- Fixed some styles like to match the styles.

- Removed DOM manupulation as string for displaying icons in `setupElementLists()` function in `setup.js`.

- Fetching the data using lifecycle hook `onBeforeMount` and storing it in proper form to display in panel body using for loop.

- Moved `createElement()` function (which creats elemets to drag on the canvas) from `ux.js` to inside vue-componet

- Move the logic of searching elements inside vue-component

**To do:-** 
- [ ] Refactoring of CSS for circuit elements panel

pr_body:
Fixes: #8 
Tasks to be done :-

- [x]  Seperate the Properties panel into its own component.
- [x]  Move the logic from showProperties() function inside Vue component to display the panel accordingly.
- [x]  There are 3 types of Properties Panel Body
> - [x]  1. Properties Panel showing Project Properties 
> - [x]  2. Properties Panel showing Circiut Element Properties
> - [x]  3. Properties of elements in Layout Mode
- [x]  Link each of the options in the properties panel to their functionality
- [ ]  Refactoring of CSS

& all places where we import and alias can be used ..', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 10, 45, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'abstrekt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917377784, 'comment_body': 'can you tell me more about this panelType == 1?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 10, 57, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'abstrekt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917378024, 'comment_body': 'If at a time, only one of these PanelType is to be rendered, then it is best practice to chain v-if with v-else-if.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 11, 0, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'abstrekt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917378458, 'comment_body': 'Lets add proper names to `PanelType1` , `PanelType2`, `PanelType3`, & use alias for any import.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 11, 3, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'abstrekt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917379857, 'comment_body': 'why was toRaw necessary here?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 11, 16, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'abstrekt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917381330, 'comment_body': "1/ lets use proper variable names here, 2/ storing props item in a variable like this removes the reactivity, are we intentionally removing reactivity? 3/ you can do something like `const { obj } = toRefs(props)` to store props in a variable and retain reactivity. 4/ also, the template can directly access all props, we don't need to extract it in the setup for the template to access props ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 11, 28, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'abstrekt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917382289, 'comment_body': 'just some tips: you can checkout JS Optional Chaining feature.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 11, 35, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'abstrekt', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917416541, 'comment_body': "Okay, I will. But I don't think any code will be left in this at the end. All of them will be moved to their respective components. ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 16, 14, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917418627, 'comment_body': 'This would be the Layout Panel and the properties of the layout elements on selecting ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 16, 34, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917418760, 'comment_body': 'Okay will change it', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 16, 35, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917420140, 'comment_body': 'assigning an object to data property it converts into proxy object. I found out Vue 3 is using [ES6 Proxy](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Proxy) to make an objects reactive I was not able to compare `propertiesPanelObj` with `simulationArea.lastselected` to prevent updating panel type every time. So used `toRaw()` to return the original object from proxy maintaining reactivity. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 10, 16, 45, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 918652594, 'comment_body': 'Thanks, I implemented it for help link', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 7, 44, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 918654458, 'comment_body': 'Yes, I renamed it and also restructured the component folder structure.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 7, 47, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 918655497, 'comment_body': 'yes, I replaced it in all the places inside the properties panel.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 7, 48, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 918657087, 'comment_body': 'I used `obj` because it was used previously in `ux.js`, will change it if required.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 7, 49, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'devartstar', 'type': 'User'}]
